### Description

**Original issue**: https://github.com/angular/angular/issues/18894

Example stack blitz: https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-5fsrdu?file=src/main.ts

Minimal reproduction Code: 
```ts
const token = new InjectionToken('token');

@Component({
  selector: 'my-app',
  template: `
    {{values}}
  `,
  providers: [
    {
      provide: token,
      useValue: 2,
      multi: true,
    },
  ],
})
export class App {
  name = 'Angular';

  values = inject(token);
}

@NgModule({
  imports: [CommonModule, BrowserModule],
  declarations: [App],
  bootstrap: [App],
  providers: [
    {
      provide: token,
      useValue: 1,
      multi: true,
    },
  ],
})
export class AppModule {}

platformBrowserDynamic()
  .bootstrapModule(AppModule)
  .catch((err) => console.error(err));
```

**Expected**: the component provider should be added to the module providers as they are both set to multi. The printed value should be "1, 2"

**Actual**: the component level provider is overriding, so the only value is "2". 

The original issue was closed without explaining why this is not a bug. This seems like a very problematic behavior to me. 

