### Anything else?

This is also reproducing with lazy loaded modules: https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-5fsrdu?file=src/main.ts

Seems like it's a more general issue that injection of a multi provider stops at the current Injector, while I expect it to go to the parent injector.

For example:

```
.my-el {
  @include mat.checkbox-theme(...);
}
```

should emit the token values on `.my-el`, not `.my-el .mat-mdc-checkbox`

